<HEAD>Former NYC Mayor Back In Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Mayor John V. Lindsay, who underwent heart
surgery a year ago, was hospitalized again for tests.
   Lindsay, 67, was in stable condition this morning in the coronary
intensive-care unit of New York Hospital, where he was admitted
Monday, said Barry Kreisberg, a hospital administrator.
   He declined further comment other than to say Lindsay was
undergoing tests.
   Lindsay underwent a 4{-hour operation at Columbia-Presbyterian
Medical Center on Jan. 27 to repair a leaky heart valve.
   He represented Manhattan's ``Silk Stocking'' 17th Congressional
District from 1959 until he was elected mayor in 1965 on a
Republican-Liberal ticket. He won his second term as an independent
and later switched to the Democratic Party.
   Lindsay practices law in Manhattan at the firm of Webster and
Sheffield.
