<FIRST>r a PM-SkiMaskRapist     03-08 0387</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Ski Mask Rapist,0398</SECOND>
<HEAD>Guilty Verdict in `Ski Mask Rapist' Case</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Note contents of last graf.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man convicted of being the ``ski mask
rapist'' in the sexual assaults of 26 women is virtually assured of
spending the rest of his life in prison, a prosecutor said.
   Anthony Sanchez, a 27-year-old former city sewer worker, was
found guilty Tuesday of 117 of 136 charges stemming from the
assaults.
   ``If I just look at the violent sexual offenses, I can see that
he's looking at more than 500 years in prison,'' prosecutor Margo
Smith said. Disregarding appeals, Sanchez would have to serve at
least half his sentence before being eligible for parole.
   ``We have a number of victims here who were greatly traumatized.
There can be no doubt justice has been done,'' Smith said.
   Superior Court Judge Paul R. Teilh set sentencing for April 25.
   Teilh said he had carefully reviewed preliminary hearing
transcripts and found no doubt that Sanchez was guilty of most of
the counts filed against him.
   Sanchez agreed Friday to let the judge declare a verdict based on
the transcripts, which included testimony from the victims. Teilh
dismissed 19 charges.
   Police reports said Sanchez usually stalked his victims before
accosting them and often tied them up, sexually assaulting them,
then taking cash, jewelry or automatic bank-teller cards. The rapes
occurred in both homes and offices and one woman was attacked in a
church confessional.
   The assailant usually wore a ski mask and often threatened his
victims with a knife or pellet gun that closely resembled a
.45-caliber pistol.
   ``I've killed before, and I'll kill again,'' he warned them,
according to the police reports.
   When Sanchez was arrested Dec. 16, 1987, police discovered a ski
mask, a black pellet gun and a hooded sweat shirt in his car.
Several victims said their assailant had worn such a mask and shirt.
   The charges against Sanchez involved attacks from 1985 to 1987 on
Santa Clara County women ranging in age from 16 to 84.
   Teilh found Sanchez guilty on 22 counts each of rape, burglary,
and robbery.
   He also found Sanchez guilty of 23 oral copulation charges, six
assaults with intent to commit rape, 17 sexual batteries, four
instances of sodomy and one count of penetration with a foreign
object.
</TEXT>
