<HEAD>Lawyer Enters Innocent Plea For Congressman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. Rep. Donald Lukens has pleaded
innocent on a misdemeanor charge accusing him of having sex with a
teen-age girl.
   Thomas Tyack, one of two attorneys representing Lukens, R-Ohio,
entered the plea Tuesday in Franklin County Juvenile Court. Tyack
also requested a jury trial before Judge Ronald Solove.
   No date has been set for the trial.
   A grand jury on Feb. 23 indicted Lukens on a charge of
contributing to the unruliness and delinquency of a child. The
