<HEAD>Italians Set up Movie Studio in Singapore</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SINGAPORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Italian Cecchi Gori group is setting up a
$17.5 million studio in Singapore to produce English-language
movies, it was announced Wednesday.
   A subsidiary called Cecchi Gori Summit Studios (Singapore) Pvt.
Ltd. has been set up to co-produce films with North American
producers worth about $206.9 million annually, said group president
Vittorio Cecchi Gori.
   He expected directors, writers, actors and actresses to come from
Europe and the United States to work in the studio complex.
   Cecchi Gori said they plan to start filming in a year, although
the complex will be completed in two years.
   The government has granted the subsidiary pioneer status
exempting it from income tax for 10 years.
