<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Burma-Rebels     03-08 0158</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Burma-Rebels,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Burmese Rebels Rob Vehicles, Kill Four</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Burmese rebels shot and killed four people
when they robbed vehicles on a road near the Thai border Wednesday,
a witness said.
   Theng U, a 35-year-old Burmese merchant, told Thai reporters
rebels of the Karen movement attacked four vehicles including a bus
at the Karen State district of Mineego, three miles west of the Thai
border.
   Burmese government troops transported about 10 people wounded in
the attack to the hospital, he said.
   The Karen army of about 4,000 guerrillas is the strongest of a
dozen ethnic rebel groups in Burma, most fighting for greater
autonomy from the central government.
   Meanwhile, Thai border patrol police said the Karens on Wednesday
continued firing mortar rounds into the Burmese village of Myawaddy,
wounding two people. The Thais say the Karens have been attacking
the village since late February to retaliate against a government
attack on a Karen stronghold.
</TEXT>
