<HEAD>Where Senators Stand on Tower Confirmation</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Updates with Lieberman, Robb</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the latest count among senators on the
nomination of John Tower to be defense secretary, as compiled by The
Associated Press.
   Thirty-nine Republicans and three Democrats said they would vote
``yes'' for Tower. Forty-nine Democrats said they would vote ``no.''
   There are nine senators undecided or undeclared.
   There are 52 senators either declared or leaning against Tower
and 44 who have declared for Tower or are considered leaning for his
confirmation. Those said to be leaning asked not to be identified
and are listed among the undecided or undeclared.
