<TEXT>
   Share prices were higher in calm dealings at midday
Wednesday, as shares were boosted from the outset by a buy program.
   Dealers also noted strong buying in futures, which inspired a
good deal of confidence in the overall cash market.
   ``People are obviously prepared to pay a high price because they
believe we're on the way up,'' one dealer said.
   ``The market feels healthy,'' another market maker said.
