<FILEID>AP-NR-03-08-89 2125EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-WorldsofWonder     03-08 0223</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Worlds of Wonder,0230</SECOND>
<HEAD>Investor Group Names Worlds of Wonder President</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FREMONT, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A New York investor group that has agreed
to buy Worlds of Wonder Inc. announced Wednesday it plans to appoint
the former president of Mattel Electronics as president and chief
executive.
   The group named Joshua W. Denham, who served as president of
Mattel Electronics from 1979 to 1983 and most recently was president
of Wonder Products in Bosler City, La.
   Denham will assume responsibility for operating the company after
confirmation of a bankruptcy reorganization plan.
   Worlds of Wonder, which at one time had $300 million in annual
sales with toys like Teddy Ruxpin and Lazer Tag, filed for Chapter
11 protection in December 1987.
   The investor group agreed Feb. 20 to purchase Worlds of Wonder
for an undisclosed amount. The group is led by Eli Jacobs and
includes Franklyn S. Barry Jr., former president of Fisher-Price
Toys, and David Edelman, former president of Ingram Software.
   The acquisition still must be approved by the federal bankruptcy
court. The group expects confirmation of its reorganization plan in
mid-May, according to a Worlds of Wonder statement.
   Following confirmation of the reorganization plan, the current
president and chief executive officer of the company, Stephen J.
Hopkins, will return to the Connecticut management consulting firm
Nightingale &amp; Associates Inc., the statement said.
</TEXT>
