<FIRST>r f BC-PetroleumReview     03-08 0783</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Petroleum Review,0492</SECOND>
<HEAD>Total Crude Runs Decline Slightly From Week Ago</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Total crude runs to stills averaged 12,675,000
barrels daily during the week ended Friday, March 3, the American
Petroleum Institute reported Wednesday. This compared with
12,699,000 barrels daily in the previous week and 12,805,000 barrels
daily a year ago.
   Crude runs east of California averaged 10,306,000 barrels daily
compared with 10,266,000 the previous week and 10,394,000 a year ago.
   Motor gasoline production for the latest week amounted to
6,620,000 barrels a day, compared with 6,625,000 barrels a day in
the previous week and 6,768,000 a day a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline production was 5,554,000 a day
compared with 5,562,000 a day last week and 5,684,000 a day a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were
246,200,000 barrels, versus 247,950,000 a week earlier and
236,748,000 a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline stocks totaled 215,536,000
barrels compared with 215,375,000 in the previous week and
206,268,000 barrels last year.
   Daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production for
the week ended Friday was 7,957,000 barrels compared with 8,338,000
last year.
   Crude oil stocks totaled 332,881,000 barrels at the close of last
week, against 323,706,000 a week previous and 342,532,000 a year ago.
   East of California crude stocks amounted to 252,782,000 barrels,
compared with 246,142,000 a week earlier.
   Daily imports east of California for the week ended Friday were
crude oil, 5,938,000 barrels, residual fuel oil, 617,000, distillate
fuel oil, 444,O00, and others 1,419,000, a total of 8,418,000
barrels.
   California imports were: crude oil 334,000 barrels, and products
82,000, a total of 416,000 barrels, for a grand total of 8,834,000.
   For the four weeks, daily imports east of California were crude
oil 5,001,000 barrels, residual fuel oil 320,000, distillate fuel
oil 228,000, and others 779,000, for a total of 6,328,000 barrels.
   For the four weeks, California daily imports averaged for crude
oil 196,000 barrels, products 77,000, a total of 273,000 barrels,
for a grand total of 6,601,000.
   The following table shows comparative daily production of the
other principal refined products for the U.S. as a whole and east of
California. Also shown are the comparative stock totals for certain
refined products.
